{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"large bowl, non-stick angel food cake pan (9 in.-10 in.), oven","id":"r105489","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-O8157XZ8uf8\/XZWrcJ3oPbI\/AAAAAAAAfnY\/Dc1DnYCMZdwhcWMj9nfiF5iwAyjmAuTnwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lco4zYsD3rd7cBDF.png","title":"Angel Food Cake","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"10 oz sugar"},{"content":"4 ½ oz cake flour"},{"content":"¼ tsp salt              (optional)"},{"content":"10 egg whites, (approx.14-15 oz), room temperature"},{"content":"1 ½ tsp cream of tartar"},{"content":"1 tsp vanilla sugar, homemade (see Tip)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"626 kJ \/ 150 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 350°F."},{"content":"Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Set scale to zero, then using a spoon, remove 5 oz of ground sugar (scale will show minus '- 5.0 oz') and reserve."},{"content":"Add flour and salt and aerate <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla sugar (see Tip) into mixing bowl and without measuring cup whip <b>4 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<b>."},{"content":"Again, without measuring cup whip <b>4-6 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<b> slowly adding reserved ground sugar 1 tbsp at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid until soft peaks form."},{"content":"Add beaten egg whites to reserved flour and gently fold in with spatula."},{"content":"Transfer mixture into angel food cake pan and bake immediately for 35-40 minutes (350°F) until a skewer comes out clean and cracks appear dry. Invert pan and allow to cool completely (approx. 3 hours). Once cool unmold onto a platter and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Cake texture is at its best when consumed within one day. To prevent from drying out, store in a container in the refrigerator. Angel Food Cake will keep for 4-5 days in the refrigerator or up to 1 month in the freezer.<br>If you don't have an angel food cake pan you can use a cake or tube pan and invert it over a bottle or a funnel to let angel food cake cool down.","Make your vanilla sugar before you start the recipe following the Vanilla Sugar recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","Angel Food Cake leftovers can be used for the cake base of trifle."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 10m","12 slices"]}